the recalibration is appropriate


509
00:19:42,281 --> 00:19:44,417 line:-1
and how it helps their care.


510
00:19:44.417 --> 00:19:46.118 line:-1 position:50%
For the Walking Steadiness metric,


511
00:19:46.118 --> 00:19:47.853 line:-1 position:50%
the requirements
to get an estimate


512
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:49,955 line:-1
should be clearly communicated.


513
00:19:49,955 --> 00:19:51,390 line:-1
Working with domain experts,


514
00:19:51.390 --> 00:19:53.592 line:-1 position:50%
like physicians
or physical therapists,


515
00:19:53.592 --> 00:19:55.628 line:-1 position:50%
will ensure that you collect
the most meaningful data


516
00:19:55.628 --> 00:19:57.329 line:-1 position:50%
from these metrics.


517
00:19:57,329 --> 00:20:00,733 line:-1
Lastly, your customer should
have control of their data.


518
00:20:00.733 --> 00:20:03.602 line:-1 position:50%
